Health Minister Joe Phahlaa launched the Keready 'I'm ready' youth vaccine drive. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The youth must be allowed to drive vaccines for young people. That's the message from Health Minister Joe Phahlaa as he launched the Keready 'I'm ready' youth vaccine drive. WATCH: COVID-19 Vaccine | Vaccination of under 12s being reviewed Phahlaa says his department is ready to work with other sectors or groups for vaccine awareness campaigns to assist the country reach herd immunity. * eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports.